## **10.5  Request ID Correlation Flow**

| Step | Action | Details |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| **1** | Request Arrives | RequestIdMiddleware runs. Generates 12-char UUID: str(uuid.uuid4())\[:12\]. Stored in ContextVar — thread-safe and async-safe. |
| **2** | Request ID Stamped | RequestIdFilter (attached to root logger) calls get\_request\_id() on every LogRecord. All log lines emitted during this request carry the same request\_id. |
| **3** | Trace Context Added | JsonFormatter soft-imports OpenTelemetry and reads the active span. Adds trace\_id and span\_id to the JSON log record, linking it to the Tempo trace for this request. |
| **4** | Exported to Loki | \_TruncatingHandler sends the log record to Loki with request\_id as a structured field. Search: {service\_name="af-license-agreement-171817", component="ui"} | json | request\_id="\<id\>" |
| **5** | Response Header | RequestIdMiddleware appends X-Request-ID: \<id\> to the HTTP response. Client can correlate frontend errors to backend log lines using this header. |

